# Salesforce Apex Conventions

## Apex Classes

- Use `with sharing` on all classes unless explicitly required otherwise.
- InvocableMethod classes use inner `ActionRequest` / `ActionResult` wrapper classes.
- SOQL: no inline comments inside queries (causes compilation failures).
- All Apex metadata uses API version 65.0.

## Deployment Checklist

1. Add class to `manifest/package.xml` under `<name>ApexClass</name>`.
2. Deploy: `sf project deploy start --manifest manifest/package.xml --target-org r6pitt1`
3. If new fields are referenced, ensure they exist in the permission set.
4. Update `dev-assets/changelog.md` with deploy ID and component summary.

## Field API Names (org-verified)

Standard objects use their API names directly. Custom objects:
- `Reservation__c`, `Restaurant_Table__c`, `Restaurant_Slot__c`
- Knowledge articles: `FAQ__kav` (org-specific — other orgs may differ)

## Formula Fields (read-only, never set in Apex)

- `Account.Logic_State__c` — calibrated confidence state
- `Reservation__c.Is_Locked__c` — 1-hour lockout gate
